<TITLE> 6 die in Sreemongol hill collapse </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moulavibazar, May 18 (bdnews24.com)Six people including five of a family died from a landslide at Sreemongal in Moulavibazar early on Monday. Five of a family were killed early on Monday after a chunk of earth from the nearby hill collapsed in a heap on their shanty in the Lakhai tea garden slum at Sreemangal in Moulavibazar. The dead were named as Sufia Begum, 45, her two sons Sumon, 14, and Sujon, 12, daughter Parveen, 24, and Parveen's husband Shamim Miah, 30. The other dead was identified as Jharna Bonarjee of Jerin Tea Garden, living at Asipara slum under Asidron Union. The hill gave in under pressure of rain-fed fountain and stormy wind at around 3:30am, Sreemangal Police Station sub-inspector Quamrul Islam said. Sufia's brother Abul Hashem told bdnews24.com that Kalighat Union Parishad member Sitaram Hajra along with the locals recovered the bodies four feet from the ground. Quamrul said the bodies were handed over to Sufia's brother without autopsy following his appeal. Jhantu Bonarjee , father of Jharna, said she died early on Monday as their house collapsed when a big chunk of earth from the nearby hill fell upon it. bdnews
